    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener>Dr Sir</opener>
                <p>I beg <persName ref="pe0274">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Smellie</persName> to
                    add my name to his subscribers if you will send me two more proposals I will
                    circulate them. He ought to insert my synonyms of each species &amp; the new
                    animals of my synopsis &amp; in particular to engrave my <rs ref="ar0331">spotted Hyæna</rs>.</p>
                <p><persName ref="pe0274">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sm.</persName> will oblige
                    me much by a set of the plates q<hi rend="superscript">to</hi> size of my <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0020">q<hi rend="superscript">to</hi> Br.
                            Zoology</title></bibl> &amp; I will chearfully pay expence of paper
                    &amp; working. Please to send the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0028">Genera of birds</title></bibl> if you can get a cheap conveyance to me
                    at <persName ref="pe0146">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Longman’s</persName>
                    bookseller in <placeName ref="pl2405">Pater noster Row</placeName>.</p>
                <p>I will inclose to you a few proofs of <persName ref="pe0058">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Cordiners</persName>
                    <rs ref="ar0236">prints</rs> which will do without giving ourselves farther
                    trouble. His work goes very soon to the press.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am, Dear Sir, <lb/>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> faithful humble
                            Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed>
                    <dateline>Dec<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 3.<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>
                        1779.</dateline></closer>

                <postscript>
                    <p>What have you done with <persName ref="pe0246">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                            Popes</persName> M.S. of <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0087">Torfæus</title></bibl> which <persName ref="pe0058">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Cordiner</persName> sent you long
                            ago.<note type="editorial">See Pennant's letter to Paton on <ref target="0247.xml">18 October 1778</ref> and notes.</note></p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
